@sen1032    How, then, does the lesser difference between varieties become augmented into the greater difference between species? That this does habitually happen, we must infer from most of the innumerable species throughout nature presenting well-marked differences; whereas varieties, the supposed prototypes and parents of future well-marked species, present slight and ill-defined differences.

              " (extract-fr) part 22 of  about: each other, other animals, second chapter, from each other, divergence of character, increase in number

