@sen1652    On the plains of La Plata, where hardly a tree grows, there is a woodpecker [Colaptes campestris] which has two toes before and two behind, a long-pointed tongue, pointed tail-feathers, sufficiently stiff to support the bird in a vertical position on a post, but not so stiff as in the typical wood-peckers, and a straight, strong beak.

