@sen3551    We have also seen that, as the specialisation of parts is an advantage to each being, so natural selection will tend to render the organisation of each being more specialised and perfect, and in this sense higher; not but that it may leave many creatures with simple and unimproved structures fitted for simple conditions of life, and in some cases will even degrade or simplify the organisation, yet leaving such degraded beings better fitted for their new walks of life.

              " (extract-fr) part 78 of  about: modified descendants, organic beings, with modification, geological record, present day, existing forms, conditions of life, throughout the world, descent with modification, nearly the same

