@sen3917    Before the last great Glacial period, no doubt the intertropical mountains were stocked with endemic Alpine forms; but these have almost everywhere yielded to the more dominant forms generated in the larger areas and more efficient workshops of the north.

              " (extract-fr) part 87 of  about: allied species, new zealand, same country, open ocean, throughout the world

@sen3918    In many islands the native productions are nearly equalled, or even outnumbered, by those which have become naturalised; and this is the first stage towards their extinction.

