              " (extract-fr) part 103 of  about: distinct species, organic beings, same species, same genus, geological record, domesticated productions, between them, long period, long run, conditions of life, forms of life, measured by years, very long period

@sen4677    The parent form of any two or more species would not be in all its characters directly intermediate between its modified offspring, any more than the rock-pigeon is directly intermediate in crop and tail between its descendants, the pouter and fantail pigeons.

              " (extract-fr) part 103 of  about: distinct species, organic beings, same species, same genus, geological record, domesticated productions, between them, long period, long run, conditions of life, forms of life, measured by years, very long period

@sen4678    We should not be able to recognise a species as the parent of another and modified species, if we were to examine the two ever so closely, unless we possessed most of the intermediate links; and owing to the imperfection of the geological record, we have no just right to expect to find so many links.

              " (extract-fr) part 103 of  about: distinct species, organic beings, same species, same genus, geological record, domesticated productions, between them, long period, long run, conditions of life, forms of life, measured by years, very long period

